** Position overview **

  * Ongoing, full-time position based at Mipac’s Brisbane head office 
  * Competitive salary commensurate with experience 
  * Flexible and hybrid work options 

** The opportunity **

As a Senior Front-End Developer at Mipac, you will focus on ensuring our
clients’ have a positive experience when using our industrial software
products. You will work closely with product owners and developers to design
and deliver exciting features with different technologies.

Free of line management responsibilities, you will provide mentorship and
guidance to other developers in this rapidly growing team and lead by example
producing succinct, robust and performant code. As a key member of the team in
this hands on position you will:

  * Be a passionate advocate for the best user experience, crafting interfaces that are as intuitive as they are beautiful; 
  * Design and implement complex ideas in a way that Engineers and Developers at all levels can understand and contribute to; 
  * Insist on high standards for code quality while respecting deadlines; and 
  * Help others leverage your expertise, by coaching and mentoring in the team. 
  * Contribute to the professional development of Engineers and Developers, improving their technical and user-interface design knowledge. 

** What’s in it for you? **

In this role, you’ll work on interesting products in complex domains, not
another boring CRUD line-of-business application. You’ll have the opportunity
to be creative and become a master of your craft, expand your mind and learn
new languages and programming paradigms in a supportive team environment. If
you enjoy a diverse workload and want to work in a position where your
recommendations make an impact, this might be a great role for you.

At Mipac, we see our people as our most valuable asset. We’re committed to
ensuring our staff feel safe, secure and comfortable, are given continuous
learning opportunities and feel valued. That’s why we offer:

  * Competitive salaries commensurate with experience 
  * Flexible and hybrid work options 
  * Continuous learning and professional development opportunities, including free access to online learning platform Udemy 
  * Support to gain further accreditation and certifications through our Study Support policy 
  * Health & wellbeing benefits including private health discounts and access to an Employee Assistance Program (EAP) 
  * Free onsite parking (conditions apply) and end-of-trip facilities in Brisbane CBD 

** About You **

Ideally, you will:

  * Comfortable thinking high-level or coding as circumstances require; 
  * Strong analytical and problem-solving skills; 
  * Able to thrive in an environment where there is ambuigity; 
  * Experience designing UI using Figma, passionate about UX, and good attention to detail; 
  * Web application development experience with React or other frameworks, modern Javascript, HTML and CSS; 
  * An interest in functional programming - maybe you have experience with Elm, F# + Fable or Elixir?; 
  * Agile software development team experience – you have experienced what works and what doesn't; and 
  * Write effective, scalable code that is easy to test and debug. 

We pride ourselves on offering an exciting and challenging place to grow your
career in an environment that allows for creativity, flexibility and support.
We believe you’ll love working with us if you:

  * Thrive collaborating with people from diverse backgrounds 
  * Welcome challenges with a can-do attitude and solution focus 
  * Value excellence and hard work 
  * Are a keen learner 
  * Value leaders who are approachable, supportive and roll up their sleeves when needed 

** About us **

Would you like to work for a global company that’s on a trajectory of
sustained growth? Are you looking for a work environment in which diversity
and inclusivity are celebrated?

Mipac is a global leader in operational technology encompassing automation,
industrial digital solutions and process optimisation. We exist to help our
clients extract maximum performance from their operations.

We have a world-leading reputation in metals and mineral processing control
and automation, with a long history of successfully delivering large scale
process control infrastructure projects and solving operational problems
through innovation.

We’ve grown rapidly and expanded into new realms within an ever‑changing,
competitive marketplace during which our core values and passion for providing
the best solutions for our clients have remained consistent. We are now
embarking on a journey of transformation, pioneering developments and
solutions in the digital sphere and continuing to evolve and enhance our solid
foundations in control systems across new industries, sectors and global
locations.

We believe every problem has a solution and are dedicated to solving even the
most complex of challenges.

For more about what we do, visit www.mipac.com.au.

